## The Acceptable Use Policy — A Practical Exercise

One of the exercises today was writing a one-line Acceptable Use Policy (AUP) for OpenMRS. Here is what I came up with:

*"All staff must use the OpenMRS system exclusively for authorized patient care activities and are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality and integrity of all patient information they access."*

Writing even one sentence at the policy level was more challenging than I expected. The temptation was to start adding specifics — but specifics belong in the standard. A policy needs to capture the intent clearly and concisely, in language that applies regardless of which specific system or technology is in use. Getting that balance right takes practice.

